msIdentifier.repository: Kislak Center for Special Collections, Rare Books and Manuscripts

msContents.summary: Collection of prayers, including several based on the Āyat al-Kursī, and several others for each day of the week.

supportDesc.extent: 150 leaves : 173 x 116 (120 x 70) mm bound to 173 x 124 mm

collation.p: Paper, 150; 1-15¹⁰. Catchwords on each page, lower left verso.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in naskh in black ink; pointed .

decoDesc.decoNote: Simple gilt headpieces, some with titles entered in red and others empty; textblock border-ruled in red; red dots with tails punctuate the text.

binding.p: Red leather over pasteboard with flap (Type II); flap does not fit the fore-edge of the textblock, possibly a re-purposed cover; blind stamped circular flowers in center, on corners and in the middle of each edge; blind-tooled frame.

origin.p: The item is undated, probably late 18th or early 19th century.

history.provenance: Sold by bookseller Thomas Thorpe to Sir Thomas Phillipps, ms. 2370 (spine label, stamp on f. 1r).
Sold at auction at Sotheby's in a sale of Phillipps manuscripts, 25 Nov. 1968, lot 242.
Deposit by Lawrence J. Schoenberg and Barbara Brizdle, 2012.
